title: leonidas_i
body:
A historical king of the [[greece|Greek]] city of Sparta, who was made popular by his fiery and hot-blooded portrayal in the movie [[300 (movie)|]].

In [[real life]] he was a very capable leader, a fierce warrior in combat and a truly honorable man. He is actually considered a national hero in Greece.

When the Persians asked the Greeks to put down their weapons at the start of the Battle of Thermopylae king Leonidas supposedly exclaimed: "ΜΟΛΩΝ ΛΑΒΕ" ([i]"Come and get them!"[/i]).

title: aspis
body:
/ˈæspɨs/; Ancient Greek: ἀσπίς

A large and round bronze [[shield]] used by the ancient [[hoplite]] Greek warriors. 

Its large size was due to the fact that it was designed to protect the user from the neck to the lower leg.  It was also intended to protect both the soldier and the comrade beside him (to the left) in a [[Phalanx]] battle formation. As such, they were always used in the left hand in those occasions.

title: mixed_media
body:
Artwork in which more than one medium or material has been employed, such as a combination of [[traditional media]] and digital (computer-based) media. 

Images where the use of traditional media isn't apparent to the viewer (e.g. traditional line art existed but was mostly obliterated by digital colors) count as neither traditional media nor mixed media. 

Likewise, if 3D assets are used, it must be apparent that they are 3D assets. If they are traced and colored over by hand, that is not mixed media. (e.g. post #5889413)

This tag can also be used for images with a 2D foreground drawing over a [[3D|]] or [[photo background|]].

title: conrail_corporation
body:
The Consolidated Rail Corporation, more succinctly known as Conrail, was an American railroad company formed in the mid-1970s following the bankruptcy of its predecessor, the Penn Central. Its principal task during its early years as a government-owned corporation was to repair and aid in the recovery of rail lines in the American Northeast and lower Great Lakes, neglected after their previous owners suffered decreasing revenue between stifling regulation and intensive competition from trucks and aircraft. Much of its early years would be spent shedding unprofitable branch lines and carrying out desperately-needed repairs on major rail arteries. The company would eventually turn a profit in the 1980s and be privatized shortly thereafter. Conrail as an independent entity would last until 1999, when it was split between the CSX Corporation and Norfolk Southern. The company exists to the present day, albeit as a "shared assets organization" managed jointly by CSX and NS to handle freight traffic in and around the ports in the New York City area. 

The company is remembered by American railfans for its particular origins, unique power (being the only railroad to order the EMD SD80MAC and having briefly run electrified operations in its early years), blue livery, and "can opener" logo.

title: eskimo_(azur_lane)
body:
[i][[Azur Lane]][/i]'s personification of the [[Royal Navy]] destroyer HMS [i]Eskimo[/i] (F75/G75). Character design by [[Shisantian]].

She is portrayed with [[short hair|short]] two-tone hair (mostly [[black hair|black]] with [[white hair|white]] [[bangs]]), and [[blue eyes]] along with [[glasses]].

Her uniform consists of a [[two-tone dress]] and a [[brown corset]] with a [[fur-trimmed capelet]] fitting of her namesake, in addition to [[red gloves]], [[pantyhose]], and red shoes. Her [[rigging]] consists of 53.3 cm quad [[torpedo tubes]] on her right and a QF 120 mm twin gun mount Mk12 on her left, with ski gear also attached to the latter side.

h4. History
She was released as a playable character as part of the [i]Counterattack Within the Fjord[/i] mini-event, a reference to her combat tour in the battles of Narvik in 1940 where she sustained severe damage (losing her bow portion) from attacking [[Z2 Georg Thiele (Azur Lane)|]]. She was repaired and later saw service in the Mediterranean and Indian Ocean before being sold for scrap in 1949.

title: izumo_(azur_lane)
body:
[[Azur Lane]]'s personification of the Japanese battleship [i]Izumo[/i], as part of a collaboration with [[world_of_warships|World of Warships]]. Character design by [[Alisa (kuro no sakura)|]], voiced by [[Ueda Reina]]. 

She is portrayed as a [[purple_hair|purple-haired]] [[oni]] sporting a samurai-inspired outfit, brandishing a large [[katana]] as a melee weapon with another sheathed. Her personality is highly-contentious, and she is verbally abusive towards the Commander in an attempt to [[tsundere|hide her true nature]].

[i]Izumo[/i] was designed with an all-forward main battery consisting of triple 16.1" guns, similar to HMS [i]Rodney[/i] and [i]Nelson[/i]. The design was ultimately abandoned in favor of the 18.1" gun-armed design that would see two ships completed as specified and sent into frontline service. The name "Izumo" would later go on to grace a class of helicopter carrier for the modern JMSDF.

In reference to World of Warships, Izumo gains improved protection against enemy AP rounds, but in turn suffers a higher chance to catch fire, similar to her WoWS counterpart.

body:
The Magellanic penguin (Spheniscus magellanicus) is a South American penguin, breeding in coastal Patagonia, including Argentina, Chile, and the Falkland Islands. Magellanic penguins are medium-sized penguins which grow to be 61–76 cm (24–30 in) tall. 

Not to be confused with [[african penguin| african]], [[humboldt penguin| humboldt]] or [[galapagos penguin]]. Magellanic penguins have two black bands around their necks instead of one.

title: african_penguin
body:
A species of penguin confined to southern African waters. It has distinctive pink patches of skin above the eyes and a black facial mask; the upper body is black and sharply delineated from the white underparts, which are spotted and marked with a black band. The pink face skin aids in temperature regulation.

This penguin weighs 4.9–7.7 lb and stands 24–28".

Not to be confused with [[humboldt penguin| humboldt]], [[magellanic penguin| magellanic]] or [[galapagos penguin]]. African penguins have a pink shade around their eyes.

title: uss_montana_(bb-67)
body:
Lead ship of the planned but never built Montana class battleship. An upgrade to the preceding Iowa-class Battleship with a speed plan of 30 knots and better armored. Wider than the maximum of the Panama Canal locks, in which larger locks were also in the plans. Both the ships and the new locks were cancelled mid war due to changing priorities in allocations of steel supplies.

In [[World of Warships]], the Montana is the top line of the U.S Battleship Tech Tree and is capable of sniping surface ships with its 406mm Triple mounts that are long range and numerous secondary gun turrets which are from the Midway-class (127mm Mk41 mounts)  capable of engaging destroyers and other cruisers. 

In [[Blue Archive]], Takanashi Hoshino helms the ship, despite being a Super Battleship type, she uses this ship for sleeping schedules.

title: lala_barina_(monster_hunter_wilds)
body:
A Temnoceran first introduced in [[Monster Hunter Wilds]].

It is a large temnoceran with a unique appearance. Its six legs are jointed and are covered in sharp-looking spikes. Its thorax and abdomen are instead coated in fluffy hairs. Its abdomen culminates in a retractable stinger, which it can use to sting enemies. The frontmost pair of legs is normally tucked within its body, but can also open up to reveal appendages that resemble clawed hands. Its head is small, with two large, orange eyes and a pair of chelicerae. Its most distinguishing feature, however, is the fact that, when enraged, part of its abdomen opens to reveal a tuft of red hairs shaped like a rose bloom.

title: gatling_gun
body:
A type of [[heavy machine gun]] with multiple rotating barrels.

The original Gatling gun was invented by Richard Jordan Gatling and first used in the [[American Civil War]] and was a direct ancestor of today's [[machine gun]]s. Though not automatic in operation, it has a hand[[crank]] for the user to [[firing|fire]] the shots and, rechamber a flesh [[ammunition]] from its [[drum magazine]], in the place of the spent cartridge, for each of its six barrels as they rotates. Gatling-style rotating barrels are still used in modern heavy machine guns such as the [[M61 Vulcan]], the [[GAU-8]], and the [[M134 Minigun]], typically to increase the sheer volume of firepower while reducing the wear of each individual barrel for continued usage.

On Danbooru, [[gatling gun]] refers to any kind of [[heavy machine gun]] with multiple rotating barrels, not just the original Civil War-era Gatling gun. If the said gatling gun were small enough to be carried by a person, then the tag [[minigun]] is applicable.

title: palm-fist_greeting
body:
A traditional Chinese greeting where the [[clenched hand|fist]] of one hand is pressed against the palm of the other.

There are two types: Gongshou Li and Baoquan Li. In Gongshou Li, the fingers cup the fist, and in Baoquan Li, the fingers are held straight out.

Gongshou Li (拱手礼), also know as [i]Fist and palm salute[/i], is a formal greeting etiquette in ancient China. It is commonly used in daily occasions (meeting and parting, when offering thanks or apologies). This greeting consists of a half-fist held in the palm of the other hand at stomach level, while [[bowing]] slightly to deeply depending on how much respect they want to convey.

Note that for males, the right-hand makes the fist and the left hand is on top. For females, it's the opposite. At a funeral, the greeting is done on the other way around: right-hand on top for men and left-hand on top for women.

Baoquan Li (抱拳礼) also know as [i]Kung Fu Salute[/i], [i]Hold palm salute[/i] or [i]Hold fist salute[/i], is a common etiquette derived from (but not exclusive to) Chinese martial arts. It shows the humility and often widely used among the kung fu masters and students. This salute is generally characterized by an open left hand placed next to a closed right fist. The importance is that the fingers on the left hand should stay extended and not flexed to cover the right fist.

A [[meme|meme format]] which refers to something in a picture which may not be seen so easily or subtly hidden. When seen, it may come as a shock to the viewer.

The Japanese equivalent on Pixiv is "おわかりいただけただろうか" or "お分かりいただけただろうか" ([i]Owakari Itadaketa darou ka[/i], 'Do you understand now?'). This phrase is from a horror TV show, ""ほんとにあった! 呪いのビデオ":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Honto_Ni_Atta!_Noroi_no_Video]" ([i]Honto ni Atta! Noroi no Video[/i], 'Cursed Videotapes Really Exist!'). When the TV staff replayed ghost videotapes sent by audiences, the phrase was used.

The exact origin of the phrase is unclear, but it likely originated from [[4chan]].

title: kitakaze_(azur_lane)
body:
[i][[Azur Lane]][/i]'s personification of the Japanese destroyer [i]Kitakaze[/i], as part of the [i][[World of Warships]][/i] collaboration. 
Character design by [[Kinjo Kuromomo]], voiced by [[Tange Sakura]]. 

She is portrayed with [[short hair|short]] [[grey hair]] and [[green eyes]], [[animal ears]], and a pet [[pigeon]] dressed in a [[serafuku]]. Her default outfit consists of a [[blue cape]], blue [[tube top]], white [[detached sleeves]], [[white skirt|white]] [[pleated skirt]], [[brown pantyhose]], [[rudder footwear]], and a yellow [[hair ribbon]]. 

Her [[rigging]] consists of several [[armor]] pieces of her hull attached to the cape, 610 mm sextuple [[torpedo tubes]] to her left, and four 100 mm twin [[anti-aircraft gun|DP mounts]] with two on each side and fashioned with [[shide]]. She also uses two [[wakizashi]] on her left rig and an [[ootachi]] as her melee weapons.

h4. Skins
* !post #3480687: Default
* !post #3612518: [[kitakaze (celebration conquest!) (azur lane)|Celebration Conquest!]]
* !post #5543731: [[kitakaze (night of doves and magic) (azur lane)|Night of Doves and Magic]]

h4. Trivia and history
She represents the V7 Project, which fixes the existing [i]Akizuki[/i]-class destroyers speed, performance and Anti Submarine Warfare; retaining the same rapid firing 10cm Type 98 with upgraded Anti air including the 40mm Type 5 Bofors installed in the existing class with the addition of the real life 610 mm quad [[torpedo tubes|torpedo launchers]] with sextuple (six-tube) launchers. Such a prototype launcher was indeed meant for [i][[Shimakaze (Azur Lane)|]][/i] but weight issues prevented this, while the intended real-life improved/simplified [i]Akizuki[/i]s were cancelled in mid-1944.

title: south_dakota_(azur_lane)
body:
[[Azur Lane]]'s depiction of the battleship USS [i]South Dakota[/i] (BB-57). Character design by [[Kaede (yumesaki kaede)|]], voiced by [[Kurosawa Tomoyo]].

Reflecting her namesake state's history with various indigenous tribes (such as the Sioux and Lakota), South Dakota is a [[Native American]] with [[dark_skin|dark skin]], [[black_hair|black hair]] done in at least two [[braid|braids]], and [[yellow_eyes|gold-colored eyes]] (possibly a reference to the presence of gold in the Black Hills region). Her personality is dutiful and protective, vowing to keep the [[Commander (azur lane)|]] safe from any threats.

She has [[long hair|long]] [[white hair]], [[rabbit ears]], [[yellow eyes|yellow]] or [[brown eyes|brown]] eyes and [[hikimayu]] (painted eyebrows). She wears a high [[black skirt]], a white top attached to it, a black [[jacket]], green-blue [[armband]], [[sleeves past wrists]], [[rudder footwear]], and a [[red bikini|red]] [[bikini over clothes]].

Her rig consists of a bow hull to her right/starboard (with an illustration of herself painted on it), with a 61 cm quintuple [[torpedo tubes|torpedo launcher]] mounted on it. To her left are two more 61 cm torpedo mounts. Her 12.7 cm twin gun mount Type D is used as a [[handgun]], and also wields a [[katana]] with the [[scabbard]] attached to the bow hull piece. 

Like [[Shimakaze (Kancolle)|]] from [[Kantai Collection]], she particularly takes pride in her speed (she attained 40.9 knots max in her sea trials), which reflects in her voice lines as well as the name of her [[playboy bunny|bunnygirl]] skin.

title: hidaka_hokuto
body:
[[Ensemble Stars!]] character. A second year student and the leader of [[Trickstar (ensemble stars!)|]].

He has [[short hair|short]] [[black hair]] and [[blue eyes]]. At school, he wears the standard [[Yumenosaki school uniform]], consisting on [[plaid pants]], a [[blazer]] and [[necktie]]. For Trickstar, he wears a [[plaid jacket]] with similar pants.

Calm, cool, and collected, Hokuto is a hard-working perfectionist. He hates when his pace is disturbed. Though he might come across as cold to his noisy classmates at first, he values his friends. He's kind and will explain things thoroughly to those who don't understand, but he's also slightly air-headed. He's very close to his grandmother and doesn't get along with his actual parents. Hokuto is also best friends with [[Akehoshi Subaru]]

He's in charge of explaining how things work at Yumenosaki to [[anzu (ensemble stars!)|Anzu]] at the beginning of the story. According to his fellow theater club member, [[Hibiki Wataru]] Hokuto stopped being "a boring person" ever since he fell in love with her. 

His voice actor is [[Maeno Tomoaki]]. His previous voice actor was [[Hosoya Yoshimasa]].

title: gentoo_penguin_(kemono_friends)
body: A [i][[Kemono Friends]][/i] character. She is one of many "Friends" in Japari Park. She is a member of the [[penguins_performance_project_(kemono_friends)|Penguins Performance Project]] idol group as "Gean" (pronounced with the soft "G" of "Gentoo", or as in "generation"). She wears a white jacket with black along the arms, shoulders and neck, a ruffled white skirt, and yellow calf-high boots. She has rusty red-orange eyes and hair highlights, and her white headphones have red-orange rings on the outer earpiece. As her design bears numerous similarities to that of her bandmate [[Humboldt Penguin (Kemono Friends)]] (Hululu), the two are sometimes mixed up by taggers. While one should be conscious of artistic liberties and stylistic differences, some reliable distinguishing details to check for include: * hair length (Hululu has shoulder-length hair, Gean's extends past her ribcage) * default outfit (Gean has a ruffled skirt; Hululu doesn't wear one, and her lower half is covered by her long jacket. Additionally, Gean's jacket has a black collar with pull-cords; Hululu has a white collar with no cords.) * default headphones (Hululu's headband is obscured by her hair at the top; Gean's is fully visible. Additionally, the design on Hululu's earpiece makes a "ç" shape, where Gean's makes a fully-closed ring.) * bangs (Gean has red streaks (sometimes depicted as a red-pink) on the sides of her center bang, usually depicted from the middle to the tip. Hululu has light pink patches on the bangs flanking the top of her center bang; her center bang just has two white dots.)

body:

Her left eye is [[one eye covered|covered]] with a white flower-shaped [[eyepatch|eye patch]] and she has two black dots [[mole under eye|below her eye patch]] (that appear to be two [[mole]]s). Her default skin features a [[short dress|short]] [[white dress]] with an [[white capelet]], [[blue bowtie]] and a [[center opening]] that indicate that she wears a [[bodystocking]] under her dress. Originally introduced in the [i]Skybound Oratorio[/i] original run as a story-only character, she was made playable with the rerun version.

In real life, she holds the speed record for a conventional hull ship at 45.02 knots during her speed trials (as against a designed top speed of 37 knots, compare [[Tashkent (Azur Lane)|]]'s 43 knots and [[Shimakaze (Azur Lane)|]]'s 40.9 knots, both also in trials.)

body:
The second remodel/kai ni of [i][[Kantai Collection]][/i]'s [[Murakumo (Kancolle)|]]. 

Upon kai ni, she ditches the sailor dress for a somewhat more elaborate white [[strapless dress]], which has vertical slits over her breasts, with a black spandex cropped t-shirt underneath. She now wears heeled [[loafers]]. Her signature [[red necktie]] is tied directly around her neck. Her [[sidelocks]] become much larger and poofier. 

Her [[rigging]] has been upgraded to be sturdier-looking. In particular, she trades her two floating 12.7 cm twin gun mounts Type B for 12.7 cm open twin gun mounts attached to her rig, one on either side. Her bridge rig on her back is also updated to match the real-life [i]Murakumo[/i]'s, but with the addition of a [[radar]] on her mast (which she never acquired in real-life). Her halo remains unchanged, but her [[rigging]] now glows blue, occasionally pink. Her mast spear is absent in her in-game portrait but other official art reveals that, while the design has otherwise barely changed as well (only the handle has moved to the middle of the shaft), it now features an actual spearhead.

body:
[[Minecraft YouTube]]r and Twitch streamer who played on [[Dream SMP]] and [[Quackity SMP]] among others, and created [[Slimecicle Cinematic Universe]].

In [[Dream SMP]], he is a centuries-old slime who lacks knowledge of the human world and becomes the pupil of [[Quackity]], who wants to make him his successor in Las Nevadas.

In [[Quackity SMP]], he is a grieving and mentally unstable father who turns to destructive actions and strange coping mechanisms to try to deal with the accidental death of his daughter, [[JuanaFlippa]].

His character is a [[slime boy]] who typically disguises himself as a human man with [[brown hair]], [[green eyes]] and [[glasses]]. His disguise is usually not very good, with either him visibly being shown as dripping or melting, or small blobs of slime being stuck to him.

title: medic_(tf2)
body:
[i]When the patient woke up, his skeleton was missing, and the doctor was never heard from again! ...Anyway, that's how I lost my medical license.[/i]

One of the playable classes in [[Team Fortress 2]], real name Dr. Ludwig.

A German man of "medicine" hailing from a lineage of mad scientists from Stuttgart, Germany (although very explicitly not a Nazi). A twisted doctor and biologist who generally considers the healing he provides an unintentional side effect of sating his own curiosity, he is known to have experimented on his teammates in bizarre, occasionally helpful ways. Despite his utter lack of morals, he provides invaluable healing for his team, and has been shown to care about them on some level, though how much of it is as his guinea pigs is debatable. Owns and cares for a number of pet [[dove]]s, chief among which is his most beloved pet, [[Archimedes (tf2)|]]. Often paired with [[Heavy (tf2)|the Heavy]], both for their gameplay synergies and in fanart.

The Medic's most important weapon is his [[medi gun]], a ramshackle tube-shaped device that projects beams of healing energy to his team. Once his medi gun has built up enough power, he can unleash the "Ubercharge", causing his patient to become fully invincible for a short period of time, shown by them becoming metallic and glowing their team's color. He also carries a [[syringe]] gun for self defense, and a [[bonesaw]] as a melee weapon. He has several alternative versions of each weapon, most notably the Crusader's Crossbow, a [[crossbow]] that fires large syringes.

The Medic's default outfit includes a large light-colored [[coat]] with buttons, team-colored rubber [[gloves]], a thick black [[belt]], black [[boots]] over team-colored pants, small round [[glasses]], and a mechanical [[backpack]] that connects to his medi gun.

Voiced by [[Robin Atkin Downes]].

title: engineer_(tf2)
body:
[i]How am I gonna stop some big, mean motherhubbard from tearing me a structurally superfluous new behind? The answer? Use a gun. And if that don't work? Use more gun.[/i]

One of the playable classes in [[Team Fortress 2]], real name Dell Conagher.

An amiable, soft-spoken good ol' boy from Bee Cave, Texas, with 11 hard science PhDs and a decade of experience in the oilfields. Like his father and grandfather before him, the Engineer specializes in inventing and constructing machines and devices, from the mundane to the scientifically fantastical. Shown to be the most laid-back and friendly of the team, although his mad scientist streak comes out in the heat of combat, as shown when he willingly cut his own hand off to wield a prototype prosthetic. Odd friends with [[Pyro (tf2)|the Pyro]], and the mortal enemy of [[Spy (tf2)|the Spy]].

The Engineer supports his team by constructing three buildings: the [[sentry]] gun that automatically fires on enemies, the [[dispenser (tf2)|]] that provides health and ammunition to his allies, and the [[teleporter]] which lets them quickly travel. His [[wrench]] is used as both a melee weapon and as a means to upgrade his buildings, and he carries a [[shotgun]] and [[handgun]] for personal defense, as well as various alternatives for each. One notable alternative is the Gunslinger, a [[single_mechanical_hand|mechanical hand]] that allows him to build "mini" sentry guns.

The Engineer's default outfit includes a yellow [[hard hat]], black [[goggles]], black [[overalls]] over a team-colored shirt, a thick [[belt]] with several pouches, yellow [[knee pads]], and black [[boots]]. He also wears one yellow rubber [[gloves|glove]] that hides the Gunslinger, and often carries his buildings in a team-colored [[toolbox]] when on the field.

Steven Thomas, known online as Steve1989MREInfo or Steve1989, is an American YouTuber and military ration commentator.

Steve began his YouTube channel in November 2015 and first gained notoriety in January 2016 for a video in which he ate 61-year-old peanut butter from a Korean War-era Meal, Ready-to-Eat (MRE). Later that year, a video review of Steve eating American Civil War-era hardtack from 1863 went viral.

Despite eating rations that are well beyond the recommended shelf life specified by Natick Laboratories and other manufacturers, Steve has reported that he rarely becomes ill, though he did contract E. coli and had to be hospitalized in 2015, ironically from a ration that was actually within its shelf life.

title: kyuudou
body:
Traditional Japanese [[archery]] is called Kyuudou (弓道). The [[bow_(weapon)|]], called a [[yumi (bow)|]], is constructed in a very special way such that it can be easily used while riding on a horse. This is done by modifying the design of the bow itself such that the main point of recurve on the bow is below its center.  

The bow itself will be quite long, yet the arrow is still fired in the same manner as the English long bow; its main difference being the lower firing position and the bow usually extend several feet above the archer's head.

title: emoji
body:
Emoji are Unicode characters designed to represent pictograms and [[emoticon|emoticons]]. The term itself, however, is most often used to refer to the pictograms and emoticons themselves. The word "Emoji" comes from the Japanese word "絵" ([i]e[/i], "picture") + "文字" ([i]moji[/i], "character"). Its resemblance to the word "emoticon" is purely coincidental.

Emoji as we know them originated as a proprietary system by a Japanese mobile phone operator [[NTT DoCoMo]] using a Unicode private-use block to encode their emoticons. While other mobile providers used many other systems for emoji, this system was the most compact implementation used at the time (and the closest to the current one).

The very first Emoji were actually Unicode Dingbats, of which, quite a few are now official Emoji. Emoji became a standardized system with its implementation in Unicode 6.0 in 2010 but it's only around 2014-2015 that their use exploded and became commonplace to the point that they became a cultural phenomenon with real world merchandise and even a movie about them.

title: millennium_ring
body:
One of the seven Millennium Items from [[Yu-Gi-Oh!]]. It has an ability to guide its owner to whatever they seeks, including another Millennium Items. As well as an ability to manipulate and sealing one's soul inside other object.

It is a dreamcatcher decorated with a triangular plate at the center and five prongs at the bottom, to which the user worn the item like a necklace.

It is possessed by [[Bakura Ryou]], whose the item would corrupted him into his evil self known as [[Yami Bakura]] [spoiler]due to it possessing the soul of the evil spirit [[Zorc Necrophades]][/spoiler].

title: millennium_eye
body:
One of the seven Millennium Items from [[Yu-Gi-Oh! Duel Monsters]] in the shape of a golden eyeball. It was notably posessed by [[Pegasus J Crawford]], who wore it in place of his left eye.

Granted the user the "Mind Scan" ability, allowing them to read the thoughts of others.

title: yamaguchi_momoe_(singer)
body: Momoe Yamaguchi is a Japanese former singer, actress, and idol whose career lasted from 1972 to 1980. Born in 1959 and often simply referred to by her given name "Momoe", Yamaguchi is one of the most successful singers in Japanese music, releasing 32 singles, including four number one hits (Fuyu no Iro in 1974, Yokosuka Story in 1976, Pearl Color ni Yurete in 1976, Yume Saki Annainin in 1977), and 21 studio albums. She also starred in 15 feature films and several television serial dramas.
